dc_title_s: LiDAR-Derived Tiled DSM (Hillshade) for Milwaukee County, WI 2020
dc_description_s: This data represents a LiDAR-derived tiled Digital Surface Model (DSM) (Hillshade) for Milwaukee County, Wisconsin in 2020. A Digital Surface Model captures both the natural and built/artificial features of the environment. Hillshading is a technique used to visualize terrain as shaded relief, illuminating it with a hypothetical light source. The illumination value for each raster cell is determined by its orientation to the light source, which is based on slope and aspect.
